Vice President Mike Pence delivered a speech in Cleveland, Ohio, highlighting the accomplishments of the Trump administration and the positive impact of the recent tax cuts. Pence praised the creation of nearly 3 million jobs since the election, the reduction in unemployment rates, and the growth of the manufacturing sector. He also emphasized the administration's efforts to rebuild the military, enforce immigration laws, and address the opioid crisis. Pence criticized Senator Sherrod Brown for voting against the tax cuts and other policies, and urged the audience to stay engaged and spread the message of the administration's achievements. He concluded by asking for prayers for America and expressing confidence in the future of the country.